  "body": "I use a M1 macOS computer. From https://hardhat.org/tutorial/setting-up-the-environment.html, I follow the instruction of Mac OS to set up the environment with these commands:\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/v0.35.2/install.sh | bash\r\nnvm install 12\r\nnvm use 12\r\nnvm alias default 12\r\nnpm install npm --global # Upgrade npm to the latest version\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen I type \"npx hardhat\" command, I end up getting error message telling me like this \"wasm code commit Allocation failed - process out of memory]\".\r\nThe best example of the error is at this stacker flow [link](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/65856300/wasm-code-commit-allocation-failed-process-out-of-memory).\r\n\r\nAfter changing to from node 12 version to node 15, \"npx hardhat\" command work for me. Please the instruction to this:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/v0.35.2/install.sh | bash\r\nnvm install 15\r\nnvm use 15\r\nnvm alias default 15\r\nnpm install npm --global \r\n```\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\n\r\nJanet",
